WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.500 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.500 --> 00:00:10.620 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:10.620 --> 00:00:13.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA GARR: Hi, I'm Lisa Garr,
host of "Gaiam Inspirations."

00:00:13.220 --> 00:00:16.140 align:middle line:84%
We are broadcasting
from Denver, Colorado.

00:00:16.140 --> 00:00:19.060 align:middle line:84%
So I'm going to give you a
few quotes from my guest, Mike

00:00:19.060 --> 00:00:23.330 align:middle line:84%
Dooley, his new book called "The
Top 10 Things Dead People Want

00:00:23.330 --> 00:00:24.110 align:middle line:90%
to Tell You."

00:00:24.110 --> 00:00:26.640 align:middle line:84%
In other words, if
dead people could talk,

00:00:26.640 --> 00:00:28.190 align:middle line:90%
this is what they would say.

00:00:28.190 --> 00:00:31.480 align:middle line:90%
They would say, we're not dead.

00:00:31.480 --> 00:00:33.340 align:middle line:90%
We are here.

00:00:33.340 --> 00:00:36.830 align:middle line:84%
We are ready for
this, but you're not.

00:00:36.830 --> 00:00:39.150 align:middle line:84%
I'm paraphrasing a
few of them here.

00:00:39.150 --> 00:00:43.860 align:middle line:84%
Your dreams really
can come true.

00:00:43.860 --> 00:00:45.590 align:middle line:84%
These sound like
the things that I

00:00:45.590 --> 00:00:49.010 align:middle line:84%
would want to hear from my
best friend, much less somebody

00:00:49.010 --> 00:00:50.630 align:middle line:90%
who has crossed over.

00:00:50.630 --> 00:00:53.160 align:middle line:84%
Joining me is international
bestselling author,

00:00:53.160 --> 00:00:53.690 align:middle line:90%
Mike Dooley.

00:00:53.690 --> 00:00:58.810 align:middle line:84%
He has over 600,000 people on
his Notes From the Universe.

00:00:58.810 --> 00:01:02.210 align:middle line:84%
These are free postings that
come in your email box right

00:01:02.210 --> 00:01:04.140 align:middle line:84%
at the right time,
just as if Mike's

00:01:04.140 --> 00:01:05.640 align:middle line:90%
looking over your shoulder.

00:01:05.640 --> 00:01:06.850 align:middle line:90%
So great to have you here.

00:01:06.850 --> 00:01:08.230 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much
for joining me.

00:01:08.230 --> 00:01:09.910 align:middle line:84%
>>MIKE DOOLEY: Thanks
Lisa, great to be here.

00:01:09.910 --> 00:01:10.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, tell
me first of all

00:01:10.810 --> 00:01:12.184 align:middle line:84%
about the Notes
for the Universe,

00:01:12.184 --> 00:01:15.090 align:middle line:84%
because they are
so wildly popular,

00:01:15.090 --> 00:01:18.966 align:middle line:84%
and 600,000 people receive
those every single day.

00:01:18.966 --> 00:01:19.660 align:middle line:90%
>>DOOLEY: Yeah.

00:01:19.660 --> 00:01:22.630 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What is your
ritual in writing those?

00:01:22.630 --> 00:01:25.110 align:middle line:84%
Where do you come up
with these really great

00:01:25.110 --> 00:01:28.160 align:middle line:90%
poignant, timely phrases?

00:01:28.160 --> 00:01:29.610 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: Well,
in the beginning,

00:01:29.610 --> 00:01:31.400 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to receive
something like this.

00:01:31.400 --> 00:01:34.100 align:middle line:84%
I started writing at a
really low time in my life.

00:01:34.100 --> 00:01:36.400 align:middle line:90%
I was looking for my place.

00:01:36.400 --> 00:01:38.670 align:middle line:84%
We had just
liquidated a company.

00:01:38.670 --> 00:01:42.900 align:middle line:84%
And they were just simply
motivation from Mike,

00:01:42.900 --> 00:01:44.280 align:middle line:84%
notes from Mike
in the beginning.

00:01:44.280 --> 00:01:48.950 align:middle line:84%
And those were never as
popular as when I finally

00:01:48.950 --> 00:01:51.050 align:middle line:84%
capitulated to
this inner feeling

00:01:51.050 --> 00:01:53.130 align:middle line:84%
of writing from the
universe's perspective.

00:01:53.130 --> 00:01:55.730 align:middle line:84%
Because I could then
say more and let it

00:01:55.730 --> 00:01:58.840 align:middle line:84%
be more impactful if it was
the universe, rather than

00:01:58.840 --> 00:02:00.840 align:middle line:84%
some dude, Mike,
who is he anyway,

00:02:00.840 --> 00:02:04.270 align:middle line:84%
writing to complete
strangers around the world.

00:02:04.270 --> 00:02:07.830 align:middle line:84%
And once I started
writing as the universe,

00:02:07.830 --> 00:02:10.340 align:middle line:90%
I saw the levity, the fun of it.

00:02:10.340 --> 00:02:12.630 align:middle line:84%
It's not something I
take overly seriously.

00:02:12.630 --> 00:02:14.070 align:middle line:90%
I'm not the mouthpiece--

00:02:14.070 --> 00:02:16.410 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: For the universe.

00:02:16.410 --> 00:02:18.630 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: It's
exploded in popularity.

00:02:18.630 --> 00:02:23.970 align:middle line:84%
And I have developed kind of
a writing style ritual, if you

00:02:23.970 --> 00:02:29.800 align:middle line:84%
will, that's similar
or parallels what I

00:02:29.800 --> 00:02:32.190 align:middle line:90%
teach in "Deliberate Creation."

00:02:32.190 --> 00:02:34.200 align:middle line:84%
Number one, all
manifestations come

00:02:34.200 --> 00:02:36.580 align:middle line:84%
about when you have
an end result in mind,

00:02:36.580 --> 00:02:38.250 align:middle line:90%
and you act on it.

00:02:38.250 --> 00:02:41.230 align:middle line:84%
And so for one minute,
prior to writing,

00:02:41.230 --> 00:02:44.790 align:middle line:84%
I get into this zone of like,
woo-hoo, I love my life.

00:02:44.790 --> 00:02:46.720 align:middle line:84%
That's the best
note I ever wrote.

00:02:46.720 --> 00:02:48.250 align:middle line:90%
This is so much fun.

00:02:48.250 --> 00:02:51.090 align:middle line:84%
Because writing for a
writer isn't always fun.

00:02:51.090 --> 00:02:52.762 align:middle line:84%
And you're like,
there's a blank screen.

00:02:52.762 --> 00:02:53.720 align:middle line:90%
What am I going to say?

00:02:53.720 --> 00:02:54.897 align:middle line:90%
How do I say it different?

00:02:54.897 --> 00:02:56.480 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: This just
happened in my life.

00:02:56.480 --> 00:02:57.960 align:middle line:90%
How do I forget that?

00:02:57.960 --> 00:02:58.930 align:middle line:90%
>>DOOLEY: Exactly.

00:02:58.930 --> 00:03:03.060 align:middle line:84%
So instead of
visualizing, I'm writing,

00:03:03.060 --> 00:03:07.280 align:middle line:84%
which is messing with the
cursed how, I advise whatever

00:03:07.280 --> 00:03:09.470 align:middle line:84%
it is you want,
life transformation,

00:03:09.470 --> 00:03:12.180 align:middle line:84%
abundance, pain
free living, imagine

00:03:12.180 --> 00:03:13.500 align:middle line:90%
that it's already happened.

00:03:13.500 --> 00:03:16.840 align:middle line:84%
So I imagine that I've already
written this really great note,

00:03:16.840 --> 00:03:19.930 align:middle line:84%
instead of imagining, today,
I'll write about gratitude.

00:03:19.930 --> 00:03:21.480 align:middle line:90%
That's boring.

00:03:21.480 --> 00:03:27.000 align:middle line:84%
So this end result then
kind of presses the

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:30.560 align:middle line:84%
how's, the means,
the inspiration,

00:03:30.560 --> 00:03:34.450 align:middle line:84%
to me, that is released and
discovered when I act on it,

00:03:34.450 --> 00:03:36.190 align:middle line:90%
just like any dream coming true.

00:03:36.190 --> 00:03:41.610 align:middle line:84%
You command the universe,
you command miracles,

00:03:41.610 --> 00:03:46.100 align:middle line:84%
if you will, for abundance,
for a career that you would do,

00:03:46.100 --> 00:03:48.866 align:middle line:84%
or whatever it is you're
after, by the end result.

00:03:48.866 --> 00:03:50.990 align:middle line:84%
Because with the end result,
the universe instantly

00:03:50.990 --> 00:03:54.400 align:middle line:84%
knows how, given all of
your other priorities,

00:03:54.400 --> 00:03:56.880 align:middle line:84%
and 7 billion co-creators,
the universe is like,

00:03:56.880 --> 00:03:58.540 align:middle line:90%
I know how to do that.

00:03:58.540 --> 00:04:01.140 align:middle line:84%
But then you need put yourself
in a place of receivership

00:04:01.140 --> 00:04:04.200 align:middle line:84%
for that transformation, whether
it's moving towards a partner,

00:04:04.200 --> 00:04:07.830 align:middle line:84%
or abundance, or in this case,
a note from the universe.

00:04:07.830 --> 00:04:11.530 align:middle line:84%
So taking action
comes from actually

00:04:11.530 --> 00:04:14.600 align:middle line:84%
writing the first stuff that
comes to mind, which always

00:04:14.600 --> 00:04:16.680 align:middle line:90%
sucks, which always is bad.

00:04:16.680 --> 00:04:20.240 align:middle line:84%
And in parallel, the baby
steps towards any dream,

00:04:20.240 --> 00:04:21.630 align:middle line:90%
they always seem futile.

00:04:21.630 --> 00:04:22.750 align:middle line:90%
They always seem pathetic.

00:04:22.750 --> 00:04:26.020 align:middle line:84%
They always seem like, I
dream of champagne and caviar,

00:04:26.020 --> 00:04:28.120 align:middle line:84%
and here I'm going to a
job I hate at the mall.

00:04:28.120 --> 00:04:29.220 align:middle line:90%
It's like, go.

00:04:29.220 --> 00:04:30.520 align:middle line:90%
Just be reachable.

00:04:30.520 --> 00:04:33.270 align:middle line:84%
That's why we have to
take these baby steps.

00:04:33.270 --> 00:04:36.270 align:middle line:84%
And by baby steps, they're the
first words to come to mind.

00:04:36.270 --> 00:04:38.700 align:middle line:84%
And then, when you
take action, it

00:04:38.700 --> 00:04:41.170 align:middle line:84%
breeds clarity in
life and in writing.

00:04:41.170 --> 00:04:42.910 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, you
have a new angle,

00:04:42.910 --> 00:04:44.500 align:middle line:84%
a new thought, let
me delete this,

00:04:44.500 --> 00:04:46.500 align:middle line:84%
let me move this here,
let me cut and paste,

00:04:46.500 --> 00:04:47.950 align:middle line:90%
let me start over.

00:04:47.950 --> 00:04:52.530 align:middle line:84%
And then, I'm in a place of
like, woohoo, I love that note.

00:04:52.530 --> 00:04:53.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You did it.

00:04:53.630 --> 00:04:55.377 align:middle line:84%
And then you sign it
from the Universe.

00:04:55.377 --> 00:04:56.960 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: I sign it
from the universe.

00:04:56.960 --> 00:04:57.980 align:middle line:90%
And it does work.

00:04:57.980 --> 00:05:01.720 align:middle line:84%
It gives me an ability to
say things that mere mortal

00:05:01.720 --> 00:05:04.740 align:middle line:90%
Mike really wouldn't say.

00:05:04.740 --> 00:05:05.592 align:middle line:90%
Believe in yourself.

00:05:05.592 --> 00:05:06.800 align:middle line:90%
You're pushed onto greatness.

00:05:06.800 --> 00:05:09.390 align:middle line:84%
Your thoughts are 10,000
times-- positive thoughts

00:05:09.390 --> 00:05:12.100 align:middle line:84%
are 10,000 times more powerful
than your negative thoughts.

00:05:12.100 --> 00:05:14.824 align:middle line:90%
If I sign that Mike--

00:05:14.824 --> 00:05:16.489 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Like, who is Mike?

00:05:16.489 --> 00:05:18.780 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: But as the Universe,
you're like, well, yeah,

00:05:18.780 --> 00:05:19.738 align:middle line:90%
that resonates with me.

00:05:19.738 --> 00:05:20.246 align:middle line:90%
Woo.

00:05:20.246 --> 00:05:21.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's great.

00:05:21.120 --> 00:05:23.370 align:middle line:84%
Do you ever feel like you
channel these, or bring them

00:05:23.370 --> 00:05:25.480 align:middle line:90%
in from the divine?

00:05:25.480 --> 00:05:27.640 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: I call it
conscious channeling.

00:05:27.640 --> 00:05:30.070 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if that
has much meaning.

00:05:30.070 --> 00:05:32.260 align:middle line:84%
But no, I don't
go into this zone,

00:05:32.260 --> 00:05:35.800 align:middle line:84%
as some channelers, where a
greater, higher self comes

00:05:35.800 --> 00:05:37.540 align:middle line:84%
through, and then
I wake up, and I'm

00:05:37.540 --> 00:05:39.510 align:middle line:90%
like, wow, what just happened?

00:05:39.510 --> 00:05:41.700 align:middle line:84%
But consciously,
I'm aware of it.

00:05:41.700 --> 00:05:43.020 align:middle line:90%
I wrangle with it.

00:05:43.020 --> 00:05:44.160 align:middle line:90%
I have intuition.

00:05:44.160 --> 00:05:45.340 align:middle line:90%
I have these feelings.

00:05:45.340 --> 00:05:49.590 align:middle line:84%
And I surprise myself with
what I write sometimes.

00:05:49.590 --> 00:05:53.480 align:middle line:84%
And I think it is channeling,
but not as most people define

00:05:53.480 --> 00:05:54.640 align:middle line:90%
channeling.

00:05:54.640 --> 00:05:57.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So let me back up a
few steps before you started

00:05:57.570 --> 00:05:58.820 align:middle line:90%
the Notes From the Universe.

00:05:58.820 --> 00:06:02.040 align:middle line:84%
What were you doing, and what
got you started on this path?

00:06:02.040 --> 00:06:05.842 align:middle line:84%
Because it definitely
wasn't always this way.

00:06:05.842 --> 00:06:07.550 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't always Notes
From the Universe.

00:06:07.550 --> 00:06:08.850 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: Well, way
back when out of school,

00:06:08.850 --> 00:06:11.590 align:middle line:84%
I was a certified public
accountant for Price Waterhouse

00:06:11.590 --> 00:06:12.970 align:middle line:90%
for six years.

00:06:12.970 --> 00:06:14.070 align:middle line:90%
I wanted more.

00:06:14.070 --> 00:06:17.340 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to be an entrepreneur,
so I sold-- not knowing

00:06:17.340 --> 00:06:18.850 align:middle line:90%
what I'd do, I quit.

00:06:18.850 --> 00:06:20.970 align:middle line:84%
Kind of forced
the circumstances.

00:06:20.970 --> 00:06:23.360 align:middle line:84%
Teamed up eventually with
my brother and mother,

00:06:23.360 --> 00:06:26.800 align:middle line:84%
and we launched type t-shirts,
Totally Unique T-shirts,

00:06:26.800 --> 00:06:30.680 align:middle line:84%
upon which was my brother's art
and my inspirational writings

00:06:30.680 --> 00:06:33.731 align:middle line:84%
about life, dreams,
and happiness.

00:06:33.731 --> 00:06:34.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: PricewaterhouseCooper.

00:06:34.980 --> 00:06:40.280 align:middle line:84%
That's a huge-- I mean,
nobody leaves that situation

00:06:40.280 --> 00:06:42.090 align:middle line:90%
without really a reason.

00:06:42.090 --> 00:06:43.190 align:middle line:90%
What was the reason?

00:06:43.190 --> 00:06:47.030 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: It was unusual,
to say the least.

00:06:47.030 --> 00:06:48.940 align:middle line:84%
I got into
PricewaterhouseCoopers,

00:06:48.940 --> 00:06:52.060 align:middle line:84%
or I got into public
accounting, because I

00:06:52.060 --> 00:06:53.780 align:middle line:90%
wanted to have a rocking life.

00:06:53.780 --> 00:06:57.180 align:middle line:84%
I was drawn to the business
world as a student,

00:06:57.180 --> 00:06:58.600 align:middle line:90%
as a teenager.

00:06:58.600 --> 00:07:00.120 align:middle line:90%
My uncle was an entrepreneur.

00:07:00.120 --> 00:07:04.439 align:middle line:84%
And all of the wise folk,
grown-ups in my life

00:07:04.439 --> 00:07:06.730 align:middle line:84%
said, you know, if you want
business world, if you want

00:07:06.730 --> 00:07:09.070 align:middle line:84%
to have a rocking
entrepreneurial life,

00:07:09.070 --> 00:07:12.060 align:middle line:84%
get an accounting degree, but
don't get stuck in accounting.

00:07:12.060 --> 00:07:13.820 align:middle line:90%
That's what they all said.

00:07:13.820 --> 00:07:15.580 align:middle line:84%
And so, I though,
all right, I like

00:07:15.580 --> 00:07:17.560 align:middle line:84%
math, so I got accounting
degree and became

00:07:17.560 --> 00:07:19.410 align:middle line:90%
a certified public accountant.

00:07:19.410 --> 00:07:23.180 align:middle line:84%
But it was to the
ends of me being

00:07:23.180 --> 00:07:27.140 align:middle line:84%
very deliberate and conscious
about shaping my life

00:07:27.140 --> 00:07:28.590 align:middle line:90%
and fortunes.

00:07:28.590 --> 00:07:33.510 align:middle line:84%
And after six years, and no one
came along and swept me away

00:07:33.510 --> 00:07:36.390 align:middle line:84%
off my feet, oh, you're the
guy we need for our company,

00:07:36.390 --> 00:07:39.130 align:middle line:84%
I thought, sheesh, I'm
going to be here forever,

00:07:39.130 --> 00:07:40.830 align:middle line:90%
stuck in accounting.

00:07:40.830 --> 00:07:44.590 align:middle line:84%
Which is an awesome profession,
particularly in that realm,

00:07:44.590 --> 00:07:45.530 align:middle line:90%
but it wasn't me.

00:07:45.530 --> 00:07:49.200 align:middle line:84%
So it wasn't that hard
to see that it wasn't me.

00:07:49.200 --> 00:07:51.299 align:middle line:84%
And since no one came
along and rescued me,

00:07:51.299 --> 00:07:52.340 align:middle line:90%
I was like, I'm quitting.

00:07:52.340 --> 00:07:56.460 align:middle line:84%
I'm just going to quit, force
the deal, trust life's magic.

00:07:56.460 --> 00:07:57.890 align:middle line:84%
And within a few
months, teamed up

00:07:57.890 --> 00:07:59.520 align:middle line:84%
with Andy, my
brother, and my mother

00:07:59.520 --> 00:08:00.970 align:middle line:90%
and launched a t-shirt company.

00:08:00.970 --> 00:08:03.080 align:middle line:90%
Which was slow going.

00:08:03.080 --> 00:08:05.080 align:middle line:84%
I thought I made the
biggest mistake of my life.

00:08:05.080 --> 00:08:09.070 align:middle line:84%
But within a year, we
were gathering momentum.

00:08:09.070 --> 00:08:11.610 align:middle line:84%
Within two, we did a
million dollars annually

00:08:11.610 --> 00:08:13.030 align:middle line:90%
for the next eight years.

00:08:13.030 --> 00:08:14.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, my gosh.

00:08:14.160 --> 00:08:15.399 align:middle line:90%
On a t-shirt company?

00:08:15.399 --> 00:08:16.190 align:middle line:90%
>>DOOLEY: Oh, yeah.

00:08:16.190 --> 00:08:18.050 align:middle line:90%
We sold them all over the world.

00:08:18.050 --> 00:08:19.549 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Full-on t-shirt company.

00:08:19.549 --> 00:08:20.174 align:middle line:90%
>>DOOLEY: Yeah.

00:08:20.174 --> 00:08:21.946 align:middle line:90%
It was t-shirts, gifts, apparel.

00:08:21.946 --> 00:08:23.570 align:middle line:84%
We branched into
absolutely everything.

00:08:23.570 --> 00:08:25.640 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I got some of
your greeting cards, which

00:08:25.640 --> 00:08:26.670 align:middle line:90%
were really beautiful.

00:08:26.670 --> 00:08:28.350 align:middle line:90%
Those are great too.

00:08:28.350 --> 00:08:31.770 align:middle line:84%
So you took this
company to another level

00:08:31.770 --> 00:08:33.960 align:middle line:90%
and came up with this TUT.

00:08:33.960 --> 00:08:34.559 align:middle line:90%
TUT.

00:08:34.559 --> 00:08:37.704 align:middle line:84%
So TUT became, other
than Totally Ultimat--

00:08:37.704 --> 00:08:39.120 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: Totally
Unique T-shirts.

00:08:39.120 --> 00:08:40.679 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Unique T-shirts to?

00:08:40.679 --> 00:08:43.179 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: Well, it then evolved
into Totally Unique Thoughts

00:08:43.179 --> 00:08:46.380 align:middle line:84%
as we broadened spectrum
of what we made available.

00:08:46.380 --> 00:08:50.590 align:middle line:84%
But by the eighth from the
year we started, the trends

00:08:50.590 --> 00:08:52.280 align:middle line:90%
were declining, it wasn't fun.

00:08:52.280 --> 00:08:53.570 align:middle line:90%
We had bought Mom out.

00:08:53.570 --> 00:08:55.790 align:middle line:84%
Andy and I were at
each other's throats.

00:08:55.790 --> 00:08:59.050 align:middle line:84%
And we thought, you know, if we
liquidate now, even though it

00:08:59.050 --> 00:09:01.230 align:middle line:84%
would be pennies on the
dollars remaining inventory,

00:09:01.230 --> 00:09:03.170 align:middle line:90%
we'd still be ahead financially.

00:09:03.170 --> 00:09:05.140 align:middle line:84%
And then we could
individually figure out

00:09:05.140 --> 00:09:08.020 align:middle line:84%
what we'll do with
the rest of our lives.

00:09:08.020 --> 00:09:09.110 align:middle line:90%
And so we did that.

00:09:09.110 --> 00:09:12.600 align:middle line:84%
And that brought on
the most harrowing,

00:09:12.600 --> 00:09:15.800 align:middle line:84%
terrifying, unpleasant
time of my life.

00:09:15.800 --> 00:09:17.570 align:middle line:90%
I was almost 40.

00:09:17.570 --> 00:09:19.750 align:middle line:84%
I was faced with
starting over, but didn't

00:09:19.750 --> 00:09:21.670 align:middle line:90%
know what I'd be starting.

00:09:21.670 --> 00:09:23.830 align:middle line:84%
They talk about the light
at the end of the tunnel.

00:09:23.830 --> 00:09:24.620 align:middle line:90%
I had no tunnel.

00:09:24.620 --> 00:09:24.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No tunnel.

00:09:24.880 --> 00:09:25.440 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:09:25.440 --> 00:09:26.940 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: It was
really, really bad.

00:09:26.940 --> 00:09:32.510 align:middle line:84%
And that's when I wished I could
receive random motivation vis a

00:09:32.510 --> 00:09:34.740 align:middle line:84%
vis this new thing
called the internet,

00:09:34.740 --> 00:09:37.480 align:middle line:84%
because it was new
in the 1990s to me.

00:09:37.480 --> 00:09:40.435 align:middle line:84%
And since nobody was sending
it out that I knew of,

00:09:40.435 --> 00:09:43.190 align:middle line:84%
I thought you know,
maybe those people who

00:09:43.190 --> 00:09:46.160 align:middle line:84%
signed our store's guest
books and left their email

00:09:46.160 --> 00:09:49.000 align:middle line:84%
addresses wouldn't
mind hearing from me

00:09:49.000 --> 00:09:51.270 align:middle line:84%
on the nature of reality,
the same kind of stuff that

00:09:51.270 --> 00:09:52.970 align:middle line:90%
was on the t-shirts.

00:09:52.970 --> 00:09:54.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's how you started.

00:09:54.500 --> 00:09:55.791 align:middle line:90%
>>DOOLEY: That's how I started.

00:09:55.791 --> 00:09:57.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The list in the '90s.

00:09:57.060 --> 00:09:57.910 align:middle line:90%
Oh, my goodness.

00:09:57.910 --> 00:09:58.890 align:middle line:90%
That's amazing.

00:09:58.890 --> 00:10:01.379 align:middle line:84%
You really had some
foresight there.

00:10:01.379 --> 00:10:03.170 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: Well, you
know, like Al Gore, who

00:10:03.170 --> 00:10:05.336 align:middle line:84%
invented the internet, I
thought it would go places.

00:10:05.336 --> 00:10:06.426 align:middle line:90%
I joke.

00:10:06.426 --> 00:10:08.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [LAUGHING] You did that.

00:10:08.800 --> 00:10:10.630 align:middle line:84%
We'll take a look
here at Mike talking

00:10:10.630 --> 00:10:12.720 align:middle line:90%
about thoughts becoming things.

00:10:12.720 --> 00:10:14.170 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:10:14.170 --> 00:10:17.070 align:middle line:84%
-How many of you have
heard the expression,

00:10:17.070 --> 00:10:21.330 align:middle line:84%
be careful of what you wish for,
because you just might get it?

00:10:21.330 --> 00:10:22.990 align:middle line:90%
Hands?

00:10:22.990 --> 00:10:24.830 align:middle line:90%
You've all heard it.

00:10:24.830 --> 00:10:27.630 align:middle line:84%
Now, how many of you
also believe it's

00:10:27.630 --> 00:10:30.090 align:middle line:90%
true to at least some degree?

00:10:30.090 --> 00:10:32.500 align:middle line:90%
Be honest.

00:10:32.500 --> 00:10:33.680 align:middle line:90%
OK, then.

00:10:33.680 --> 00:10:35.540 align:middle line:84%
How many of you
have therefore given

00:10:35.540 --> 00:10:38.230 align:middle line:84%
considerable time,
energy, or thought

00:10:38.230 --> 00:10:42.290 align:middle line:84%
to figuring out just how
or why it could be true?

00:10:42.290 --> 00:10:45.420 align:middle line:90%


00:10:45.420 --> 00:10:47.570 align:middle line:84%
Fortunately, having
a mother who's

00:10:47.570 --> 00:10:50.220 align:middle line:84%
always inspired me to
be a big time dreamer,

00:10:50.220 --> 00:10:52.060 align:middle line:90%
I have thought about it.

00:10:52.060 --> 00:10:54.510 align:middle line:84%
And I've come to the
conclusion that there is indeed

00:10:54.510 --> 00:10:58.870 align:middle line:84%
a principle at play in the
universe that turns wishes

00:10:58.870 --> 00:11:00.600 align:middle line:90%
into reality.

00:11:00.600 --> 00:11:03.789 align:middle line:84%
It's the exact same principle
that powers positive thinking.

00:11:03.789 --> 00:11:05.330 align:middle line:84%
And it's the very
same principle that

00:11:05.330 --> 00:11:09.660 align:middle line:84%
explains why visualizing
is an exercise practiced

00:11:09.660 --> 00:11:10.930 align:middle line:90%
around the world.

00:11:10.930 --> 00:11:15.580 align:middle line:84%
It's even encouraged in our
basic toast masters manual.

00:11:15.580 --> 00:11:20.500 align:middle line:84%
In three simple words,
that principle is this.

00:11:20.500 --> 00:11:25.316 align:middle line:90%
Thoughts become things.

00:11:25.316 --> 00:11:26.690 align:middle line:84%
And I don't mean
it figuratively.

00:11:26.690 --> 00:11:27.790 align:middle line:90%
I mean it literally.

00:11:27.790 --> 00:11:29.410 align:middle line:90%
Thoughts become things.

00:11:29.410 --> 00:11:31.960 align:middle line:90%
Not sometimes, but all the time.

00:11:31.960 --> 00:11:36.200 align:middle line:84%
And not just our positive
thoughts, but the other ones

00:11:36.200 --> 00:11:37.050 align:middle line:90%
too.

00:11:37.050 --> 00:11:40.910 align:middle line:84%
Because it's an
immutable law, as rigid

00:11:40.910 --> 00:11:45.680 align:middle line:90%
and predictable as gravity.

00:11:45.680 --> 00:11:48.600 align:middle line:84%
Now, I've known about this
principle my entire adult life.

00:11:48.600 --> 00:11:51.340 align:middle line:84%
And actually, while I'm
not really all that old,

00:11:51.340 --> 00:11:53.490 align:middle line:84%
I've had some
amazing experiences

00:11:53.490 --> 00:11:56.630 align:middle line:84%
with it, my favorite of which
began just two years after I

00:11:56.630 --> 00:11:57.752 align:middle line:90%
graduated from college.

00:11:57.752 --> 00:11:59.210 align:middle line:84%
I was working for
Price Waterhouse,

00:11:59.210 --> 00:12:02.500 align:middle line:84%
and it took me two years
with PW to finally get myself

00:12:02.500 --> 00:12:04.750 align:middle line:84%
in a position
where I could begin

00:12:04.750 --> 00:12:07.760 align:middle line:84%
thinking about thriving
in the real world

00:12:07.760 --> 00:12:10.270 align:middle line:90%
instead of just surviving.

00:12:10.270 --> 00:12:12.610 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things I did
to help me think thoughts

00:12:12.610 --> 00:12:15.410 align:middle line:84%
about thriving in
the real world was

00:12:15.410 --> 00:12:18.730 align:middle line:90%
I created a little scrapbook.

00:12:18.730 --> 00:12:21.540 align:middle line:84%
And in the scrapbook,
I put pictures

00:12:21.540 --> 00:12:24.680 align:middle line:84%
I had taken from magazines
of things that I wanted,

00:12:24.680 --> 00:12:28.080 align:middle line:84%
like a nice watch, a fancy
car, a condo, a house.

00:12:28.080 --> 00:12:30.120 align:middle line:84%
And I also put in this
scrapbook pictures

00:12:30.120 --> 00:12:34.330 align:middle line:84%
of foreign destinations that
one day, I'd like to visit.

00:12:34.330 --> 00:12:37.750 align:middle line:90%
London, Paris, Hong Kong, Tokyo.

00:12:37.750 --> 00:12:39.850 align:middle line:84%
And I used this
scrapbook to help

00:12:39.850 --> 00:12:46.170 align:middle line:84%
me visualize every conceivable
detail of my dreamed of life.

00:12:46.170 --> 00:12:49.340 align:middle line:84%
Well, I did this visualizing
experiment every single day

00:12:49.340 --> 00:12:54.170 align:middle line:84%
for a couple of weeks, and
nothing seemed to happen.

00:12:54.170 --> 00:12:57.930 align:middle line:84%
After just a couple of
months, every single day,

00:12:57.930 --> 00:13:00.830 align:middle line:90%
nothing seemed to happen.

00:13:00.830 --> 00:13:03.010 align:middle line:84%
In fact, it was almost
a full year later

00:13:03.010 --> 00:13:05.342 align:middle line:84%
when one day, I went to
work as I always did,

00:13:05.342 --> 00:13:07.550 align:middle line:84%
and for the first time,
learned that Price Waterhouse

00:13:07.550 --> 00:13:11.230 align:middle line:84%
every year sends a few
select people overseas

00:13:11.230 --> 00:13:12.776 align:middle line:90%
on foreign assignments.

00:13:12.776 --> 00:13:16.160 align:middle line:90%


00:13:16.160 --> 00:13:23.750 align:middle line:84%
Six weeks later , I was
living in sunny Saudi Arabia.

00:13:23.750 --> 00:13:28.070 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:13:28.070 --> 00:13:29.710 align:middle line:84%
Which to a couple of
you here might not

00:13:29.710 --> 00:13:31.100 align:middle line:90%
sound like a dream come true.

00:13:31.100 --> 00:13:33.360 align:middle line:84%
And I have to admit, I
had not spent any time

00:13:33.360 --> 00:13:35.820 align:middle line:84%
visualizing myself living
in the Middle East.

00:13:35.820 --> 00:13:38.250 align:middle line:84%
Never even heard of Riyadh
six weeks prior to making it

00:13:38.250 --> 00:13:40.495 align:middle line:90%
my home.

00:13:40.495 --> 00:13:43.415 align:middle line:84%
But I had been visualizing
my dreamed of life,

00:13:43.415 --> 00:13:45.790 align:middle line:84%
and I don't think anything
else could have taken me there

00:13:45.790 --> 00:13:49.520 align:middle line:84%
quicker at that point in my life
than this 18 month tour of duty

00:13:49.520 --> 00:13:50.930 align:middle line:90%
to Saudi Arabia.

00:13:50.930 --> 00:13:54.400 align:middle line:84%
Because while I was there,
I earned a very considerable

00:13:54.400 --> 00:13:59.530 align:middle line:84%
hardship bonus, and I
accrued three months

00:13:59.530 --> 00:14:03.660 align:middle line:84%
paid time off to go wherever
and whenever I wanted.

00:14:03.660 --> 00:14:08.480 align:middle line:84%
And during those three months,
I went to every city and country

00:14:08.480 --> 00:14:11.890 align:middle line:84%
on God's green earth
that I had ever

00:14:11.890 --> 00:14:15.690 align:middle line:84%
dreamed of going
throughout Africa, Asia,

00:14:15.690 --> 00:14:17.510 align:middle line:90%
the Far East, the South Seas.

00:14:17.510 --> 00:14:20.560 align:middle line:90%


00:14:20.560 --> 00:14:25.100 align:middle line:84%
And my heart nearly
missed a beat one morning,

00:14:25.100 --> 00:14:28.690 align:middle line:84%
having breakfast at the regent
hotel in Kowloon, Hong Kong,

00:14:28.690 --> 00:14:30.240 align:middle line:84%
when I looked up
from over my coffee

00:14:30.240 --> 00:14:33.690 align:middle line:84%
through the two-story plate
glass wall that surrounded me,

00:14:33.690 --> 00:14:40.070 align:middle line:84%
and saw the exact same
view of Hong Kong Island

00:14:40.070 --> 00:14:43.030 align:middle line:84%
that I had cut and pasted into
my little scrapbook just two

00:14:43.030 --> 00:14:45.100 align:middle line:90%
years earlier.

00:14:45.100 --> 00:14:46.950 align:middle line:84%
I could go on and on
to, sharing with you

00:14:46.950 --> 00:14:51.480 align:middle line:84%
more fantastic stories,
and some really sad ones,

00:14:51.480 --> 00:14:53.880 align:middle line:84%
all illustrating how my
thoughts had become the things

00:14:53.880 --> 00:14:55.250 align:middle line:90%
and events of my life.

00:14:55.250 --> 00:14:59.290 align:middle line:84%
But you know who else
could do that, don't you?

00:14:59.290 --> 00:15:02.830 align:middle line:84%
Every single one of
you here, because it

00:15:02.830 --> 00:15:06.790 align:middle line:84%
is an immutable law that
governs all of our lives,

00:15:06.790 --> 00:15:08.310 align:middle line:90%
whether we know about it or not.

