00:16:01.160 --> 00:16:06.220 align:middle line:84%
I've always been almost obsessed
with reality, who we are,

00:16:06.220 --> 00:16:07.010 align:middle line:90%
how we got here.

00:16:07.010 --> 00:16:10.330 align:middle line:84%
As a teenager, a pre-teenager,
I would toss out things

00:16:10.330 --> 00:16:13.020 align:middle line:84%
to my mom, like time and
space have to be illusionary.

00:16:13.020 --> 00:16:14.860 align:middle line:90%
They can't be real.

00:16:14.860 --> 00:16:16.290 align:middle line:90%
God has to be in all of us.

00:16:16.290 --> 00:16:18.950 align:middle line:84%
There can't be a
hell or a devil.

00:16:18.950 --> 00:16:22.040 align:middle line:84%
These ideas don't have
any logic behind them.

00:16:22.040 --> 00:16:28.280 align:middle line:84%
And my ambition all my life
was to take these truths that

00:16:28.280 --> 00:16:33.830 align:middle line:84%
literally stirred in my
veins, and use them to have,

00:16:33.830 --> 00:16:36.500 align:middle line:90%
selfishly, a rocking life.

00:16:36.500 --> 00:16:39.690 align:middle line:84%
But as things turned and
twisted, we just talked about,

00:16:39.690 --> 00:16:42.880 align:middle line:84%
I found myself 15 years
ago like, now what

00:16:42.880 --> 00:16:44.150 align:middle line:90%
am I going to do?

00:16:44.150 --> 00:16:51.900 align:middle line:84%
And I became, I guess,
this spout of truths.

00:16:51.900 --> 00:16:53.120 align:middle line:90%
I would call them truths.

00:16:53.120 --> 00:16:55.203 align:middle line:84%
I'm not the only one that
have stumbled upon them.

00:16:55.203 --> 00:16:57.070 align:middle line:90%
Countless others have.

00:16:57.070 --> 00:16:58.410 align:middle line:90%
But they gave me a platform.

00:16:58.410 --> 00:16:59.910 align:middle line:84%
And when I went
from Notes From Mike

00:16:59.910 --> 00:17:02.740 align:middle line:84%
to Notes From the Universe,
they became really popular.

00:17:02.740 --> 00:17:05.890 align:middle line:84%
Because I really do feel
like life is knowable.

00:17:05.890 --> 00:17:07.869 align:middle line:90%
There are absolute truths.

00:17:07.869 --> 00:17:10.869 align:middle line:84%
They're not little
fuzzy, gray, everyone

00:17:10.869 --> 00:17:14.329 align:middle line:84%
has their own truth, boom,
there goes your power.

00:17:14.329 --> 00:17:16.410 align:middle line:84%
With regard to who we
are and how we got here,

00:17:16.410 --> 00:17:20.400 align:middle line:84%
there is no grey area, and it
doesn't matter what a million

00:17:20.400 --> 00:17:21.260 align:middle line:90%
people say.

00:17:21.260 --> 00:17:24.290 align:middle line:84%
We are of the eyes and
the ears of the divine.

00:17:24.290 --> 00:17:25.630 align:middle line:90%
We are here by choice.

00:17:25.630 --> 00:17:27.240 align:middle line:90%
We are pushed onto greatness.

00:17:27.240 --> 00:17:29.010 align:middle line:84%
Our positive thoughts
are more powerful

00:17:29.010 --> 00:17:30.310 align:middle line:90%
than negative thoughts.

00:17:30.310 --> 00:17:32.170 align:middle line:84%
And these are the things
that just gush out

00:17:32.170 --> 00:17:35.010 align:middle line:84%
of me all the time,
and that I mull over

00:17:35.010 --> 00:17:38.740 align:middle line:84%
from every single angle with
the greatest amount of glee.

00:17:38.740 --> 00:17:41.050 align:middle line:84%
And it was a Note From
the Universe that was once

00:17:41.050 --> 00:17:43.530 align:middle line:84%
titled about three
years ago, just

00:17:43.530 --> 00:17:47.940 align:middle line:84%
on a whim I had this idea,
after my little woohoo exercise,

00:17:47.940 --> 00:17:49.840 align:middle line:84%
I wrote something that
was like, "And That's

00:17:49.840 --> 00:17:51.220 align:middle line:90%
What the Dead Want You to Know."

00:17:51.220 --> 00:17:52.969 align:middle line:84%
And it was like, oh,
let's work with this.

00:17:52.969 --> 00:17:53.850 align:middle line:90%
That's fun.

00:17:53.850 --> 00:17:56.615 align:middle line:84%
And it ended up
being, Lisa, at these

