>>DOOLEY: That I have
found that I truly

00:18:34.420 --> 00:18:38.000 align:middle line:84%
believe the dead
have died to tell us,

00:18:38.000 --> 00:18:39.420 align:middle line:90%
in a manner of speaking.

00:18:39.420 --> 00:18:42.360 align:middle line:84%
Because they have a
heightened vantage

00:18:42.360 --> 00:18:45.000 align:middle line:90%
point, the old souls at least.

00:18:45.000 --> 00:18:46.730 align:middle line:90%
Not the new souls.

00:18:46.730 --> 00:18:49.710 align:middle line:84%
They're still chasing demons,
no doubt, on the other side,

00:18:49.710 --> 00:18:51.990 align:middle line:84%
and getting ready
for their next turn.

00:18:51.990 --> 00:18:55.440 align:middle line:84%
But the dead would want us
to know that they're well.

00:18:55.440 --> 00:18:57.510 align:middle line:90%
That everything's OK.

00:18:57.510 --> 00:19:01.070 align:middle line:84%
It's OK to let go,
to stop the grieving,

00:19:01.070 --> 00:19:04.180 align:middle line:84%
to celebrate their life, and
begin enjoying your life.

00:19:04.180 --> 00:19:05.790 align:middle line:84%
Because from where
they are, they

00:19:05.790 --> 00:19:07.480 align:middle line:90%
can see these absolute truths.

00:19:07.480 --> 00:19:11.680 align:middle line:84%
They can see that life
is a banquet, where

00:19:11.680 --> 00:19:13.440 align:middle line:84%
we get to choose our
thoughts, thoughts

00:19:13.440 --> 00:19:15.330 align:middle line:90%
that will then become things.

00:19:15.330 --> 00:19:16.870 align:middle line:90%
And on and on and on.

00:19:16.870 --> 00:19:19.670 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The one
about, we're OK, it's

00:19:19.670 --> 00:19:23.350 align:middle line:84%
we are ready to die,
basically, but you're not.

00:19:23.350 --> 00:19:25.060 align:middle line:90%
That is beautifully said.

00:19:25.060 --> 00:19:28.290 align:middle line:84%
No one left behind is
ready for them to go.

00:19:28.290 --> 00:19:30.750 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter if
you know that your loved

00:19:30.750 --> 00:19:32.060 align:middle line:90%
one has been sick or not.

00:19:32.060 --> 00:19:34.020 align:middle line:90%
It's never the right time.

00:19:34.020 --> 00:19:37.650 align:middle line:84%
It's like, it's never the
right time to have a baby.

00:19:37.650 --> 00:19:40.060 align:middle line:84%
You're never prepared for
the amount that it is.

00:19:40.060 --> 00:19:41.805 align:middle line:90%
>>DOOLEY: Yeah.

00:19:41.805 --> 00:19:44.310 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So that's a
beautiful perspective

00:19:44.310 --> 00:19:47.930 align:middle line:84%
and comforting to those
who've lost loved ones.

00:19:47.930 --> 00:19:52.960 align:middle line:84%
If they were to come back
around and say, we're fine.

00:19:52.960 --> 00:19:55.970 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: It would be the
greatest soothing balm

00:19:55.970 --> 00:19:59.400 align:middle line:84%
imaginable for all of us
who have lost loved ones.

00:19:59.400 --> 00:20:02.030 align:middle line:84%
Because in these
primitive times that we

00:20:02.030 --> 00:20:04.950 align:middle line:84%
chose to be alive, primitive
spiritually speaking,

00:20:04.950 --> 00:20:08.980 align:middle line:84%
we are hardwired using our
physical senses virtually alone

00:20:08.980 --> 00:20:12.290 align:middle line:84%
to interpret reality,
ourselves, our journeys.

00:20:12.290 --> 00:20:16.520 align:middle line:84%
And when someone's gone to
the physical senses, I mean,

00:20:16.520 --> 00:20:17.850 align:middle line:90%
it's beyond devastating.

00:20:17.850 --> 00:20:18.960 align:middle line:90%
I mean, gone forever.

00:20:18.960 --> 00:20:20.080 align:middle line:90%
Gone to where?

00:20:20.080 --> 00:20:20.890 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:20:20.890 --> 00:20:22.920 align:middle line:84%
And it appears,
since we're not clued

00:20:22.920 --> 00:20:25.500 align:middle line:84%
into the mechanics of
all manifestations,

00:20:25.500 --> 00:20:27.740 align:middle line:90%
it often appears random.

00:20:27.740 --> 00:20:31.810 align:middle line:84%
It appears accidental, which
brings about feelings of like,

00:20:31.810 --> 00:20:34.420 align:middle line:84%
if only, and if I
didn't take the train,

00:20:34.420 --> 00:20:36.130 align:middle line:84%
if I told him I loved
him one more time.

00:20:36.130 --> 00:20:38.690 align:middle line:84%
That those opportunities
are lost forever,

00:20:38.690 --> 00:20:40.560 align:middle line:90%
and none of that's true.

00:20:40.560 --> 00:20:42.820 align:middle line:84%
It's just our
physical senses, which

00:20:42.820 --> 00:20:46.114 align:middle line:84%
are the biggest liars
in the universe,

00:20:46.114 --> 00:20:47.780 align:middle line:84%
although they serve
a valuable service--

00:20:47.780 --> 00:20:50.090 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: For survival.

00:20:50.090 --> 00:20:51.290 align:middle line:90%
>>DOOLEY: --time and space.

00:20:51.290 --> 00:20:53.270 align:middle line:84%
And they make the
adventures possible.

00:20:53.270 --> 00:20:55.330 align:middle line:84%
And they grip us
with our passions.

00:20:55.330 --> 00:20:57.320 align:middle line:84%
And they fill us
with excitement.

00:20:57.320 --> 00:20:59.370 align:middle line:84%
And they give us
a reason to live.

00:20:59.370 --> 00:21:04.270 align:middle line:84%
So there's a point to living in
the lies and misunderstanding.

00:21:04.270 --> 00:21:07.520 align:middle line:84%
But when we take it
so far unnecessarily,

00:21:07.520 --> 00:21:10.350 align:middle line:84%
to believe that the
things can happen

00:21:10.350 --> 00:21:14.650 align:middle line:84%
by chance and without meaning,
and that there's no order,

00:21:14.650 --> 00:21:16.910 align:middle line:84%
it's even more devastating
to lose someone.

00:21:16.910 --> 00:21:19.140 align:middle line:84%
So they want you to
know-- and I talk

00:21:19.140 --> 00:21:22.320 align:middle line:84%
through the various chapters
about understanding accidents,

00:21:22.320 --> 00:21:25.120 align:middle line:84%
and that there is no such thing,
however random they appear,

00:21:25.120 --> 00:21:28.110 align:middle line:84%
up here and understanding
that life is fair,

00:21:28.110 --> 00:21:32.590 align:middle line:84%
no matter how unfair
circumstances will seem to be.

00:21:32.590 --> 00:21:37.170 align:middle line:84%
And when you get these
enter glimpses of reality,

00:21:37.170 --> 00:21:41.160 align:middle line:84%
you then realize that they
didn't die, that all is well,

00:21:41.160 --> 00:21:44.960 align:middle line:84%
that order is being followed,
perfection and love abound,

00:21:44.960 --> 00:21:49.459 align:middle line:84%
and that it's still our
turn on stage, which is

00:21:49.459 --> 00:21:50.750 align:middle line:90%
what they most want us to know.

00:21:50.750 --> 00:21:54.460 align:middle line:84%
Because if you're still here,
even with stage four cancer,

00:21:54.460 --> 00:21:55.740 align:middle line:90%
you're not ready.

00:21:55.740 --> 00:21:57.770 align:middle line:90%
It is not your time.

00:21:57.770 --> 00:21:59.046 align:middle line:90%
Otherwise, you'd be gone.

00:21:59.046 --> 00:22:00.420 align:middle line:84%
When it's your
time, you're gone.

00:22:00.420 --> 00:22:00.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You're gone.

00:22:00.720 --> 00:22:02.386 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: You know,
it's just like that.

00:22:02.386 --> 00:22:05.960 align:middle line:84%
And that may seem
naive to viewers

00:22:05.960 --> 00:22:08.300 align:middle line:84%
right now who are only
using their physical senses,

00:22:08.300 --> 00:22:10.060 align:middle line:84%
but there's so much
more that we can

00:22:10.060 --> 00:22:13.690 align:middle line:84%
tap into using our inner
senses, using simple deduction,

00:22:13.690 --> 00:22:15.670 align:middle line:84%
just connecting
some dots, as I do

00:22:15.670 --> 00:22:18.170 align:middle line:84%
in the book, that
can give this comfort

00:22:18.170 --> 00:22:22.011 align:middle line:84%
and excite us with the time
that remains in our own lives.

00:22:22.011 --> 00:22:23.760 align:middle line:84%
Because we're going
to see them all again,

00:22:23.760 --> 00:22:26.070 align:middle line:84%
and we'll be together
forever and ever and ever.

00:22:26.070 --> 00:22:28.700 align:middle line:84%
But right now, may hay,
they want to tell you.

00:22:28.700 --> 00:22:29.900 align:middle line:90%
This is it.

00:22:29.900 --> 00:22:32.070 align:middle line:84%
You know, you've got
every opportunity

00:22:32.070 --> 00:22:35.240 align:middle line:84%
to discover every truth, and
live your grandest, best,

00:22:35.240 --> 00:22:36.960 align:middle line:90%
most joyful life.

00:22:36.960 --> 00:22:40.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So they say you
can create your dream.

00:22:40.900 --> 00:22:42.150 align:middle line:90%
>>DOOLEY: Dreams do come true.

00:22:42.150 --> 00:22:42.983 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I love that.

00:22:42.983 --> 00:22:46.070 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: There is a process,
and it is identifiable.

00:22:46.070 --> 00:22:50.140 align:middle line:84%
And we bear witness and truth
to it in our lives all the time.

00:22:50.140 --> 00:22:52.930 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So if we were to
imagine our ancestors,

00:22:52.930 --> 00:22:55.530 align:middle line:84%
or our past loved
ones saying, go,

00:22:55.530 --> 00:22:58.120 align:middle line:84%
do it, do that thing
you've been wanting to do,

00:22:58.120 --> 00:22:59.586 align:middle line:84%
they're like
cheerleaders for us.

00:22:59.586 --> 00:23:00.460 align:middle line:90%
>>DOOLEY: Absolutely.

00:23:00.460 --> 00:23:01.670 align:middle line:90%
Our biggest cheerleaders.

00:23:01.670 --> 00:23:03.250 align:middle line:84%
They adore us, and
they want nothing

00:23:03.250 --> 00:23:04.950 align:middle line:90%
more than a smile on our face.

00:23:04.950 --> 00:23:08.380 align:middle line:84%
And they see now what
they missed in life,

00:23:08.380 --> 00:23:12.030 align:middle line:84%
and they realize we don't
have to be so blind or naive.

00:23:12.030 --> 00:23:13.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What a perspective.

00:23:13.230 --> 00:23:15.060 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: Thoughts
become things.

00:23:15.060 --> 00:23:17.160 align:middle line:84%
Define what you want in
terms of the end result,

00:23:17.160 --> 00:23:18.576 align:middle line:84%
not how you're
going to get there.

00:23:18.576 --> 00:23:20.440 align:middle line:84%
Brain's too small to
do all the logistics.

00:23:20.440 --> 00:23:22.915 align:middle line:84%
And then in spite
of the futility,

00:23:22.915 --> 00:23:26.710 align:middle line:84%
the seeming futility,
of it, act on it,

00:23:26.710 --> 00:23:28.960 align:middle line:84%
do something, baby
step every day.

00:23:28.960 --> 00:23:31.780 align:middle line:84%
Show up, and prepare
to be astounded.

00:23:31.780 --> 00:23:34.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now, even where it comes
to someone who in this lifetime

00:23:34.700 --> 00:23:39.180 align:middle line:84%
was very sick, very ill,
once they crossed over,

00:23:39.180 --> 00:23:43.720 align:middle line:84%
your perspective is they
come at you with fervor,

00:23:43.720 --> 00:23:48.160 align:middle line:84%
with excitement, with that
cheerleader perspective.

00:23:48.160 --> 00:23:51.400 align:middle line:84%
What about-- OK, so there
was it chilling note

00:23:51.400 --> 00:23:55.270 align:middle line:84%
that you wrote in the book from
a son who committed suicide,

00:23:55.270 --> 00:23:57.260 align:middle line:90%
and the note was to his brother.

00:23:57.260 --> 00:23:59.730 align:middle line:84%
And we can't talk about
it without crying,

00:23:59.730 --> 00:24:02.290 align:middle line:90%
but it's very deep.

00:24:02.290 --> 00:24:04.820 align:middle line:90%
That was very deep.

00:24:04.820 --> 00:24:07.470 align:middle line:84%
So where did you
come up with that?

00:24:07.470 --> 00:24:09.770 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: After
every chapter, there

00:24:09.770 --> 00:24:13.170 align:middle line:84%
is a letter from a dearly
departed to someone back

00:24:13.170 --> 00:24:18.320 align:middle line:84%
home to kind of make
it real, the lessons

00:24:18.320 --> 00:24:20.050 align:middle line:84%
of that chapter,
which at times had

00:24:20.050 --> 00:24:22.170 align:middle line:90%
to be a little bit esoteric.

00:24:22.170 --> 00:24:26.470 align:middle line:84%
And that chapter that
that letter concludes

00:24:26.470 --> 00:24:31.140 align:middle line:84%
was, there is no hell
and there is no devil.

00:24:31.140 --> 00:24:35.130 align:middle line:84%
And too often, we are
taught the exact opposite,

00:24:35.130 --> 00:24:37.630 align:middle line:84%
and we're further taught
their loved ones who

00:24:37.630 --> 00:24:43.430 align:middle line:84%
choose to end their life
are met with brimstone,

00:24:43.430 --> 00:24:46.322 align:middle line:90%
and condemnation, and judgement.

00:24:46.322 --> 00:24:48.780 align:middle line:84%
So I wanted to achieve a number
of things with that letter.

00:24:48.780 --> 00:24:51.230 align:middle line:84%
First and foremost, to let
them know there is no hell,

00:24:51.230 --> 00:24:52.140 align:middle line:90%
there is no devil.

00:24:52.140 --> 00:24:57.110 align:middle line:84%
That was a bunch of malarkey
designed by people with agendas

00:24:57.110 --> 00:24:59.820 align:middle line:84%
to scare the masses
through manipulation.

00:24:59.820 --> 00:25:00.670 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Correct.

00:25:00.670 --> 00:25:04.780 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: Would a loving God put
anyone under any circumstances

00:25:04.780 --> 00:25:07.610 align:middle line:84%
into hell for eternity,
or would a loving God

00:25:07.610 --> 00:25:11.770 align:middle line:84%
so great that He could hang
the stars in the night sky,

00:25:11.770 --> 00:25:16.180 align:middle line:84%
create 100 million spectacular
species on this Earth,

00:25:16.180 --> 00:25:19.030 align:middle line:84%
wouldn't that God
be wise enough to be

00:25:19.030 --> 00:25:21.150 align:middle line:90%
able to rehabilitate anyone?

00:25:21.150 --> 00:25:24.070 align:middle line:84%
And wouldn't that God
be accountable enough

00:25:24.070 --> 00:25:27.820 align:middle line:84%
to accept responsibility for
all of his or her children's

00:25:27.820 --> 00:25:28.850 align:middle line:90%
behavior?

00:25:28.850 --> 00:25:32.250 align:middle line:84%
All of this is easy to kind
of deduce, and eliminate

00:25:32.250 --> 00:25:35.800 align:middle line:84%
this fictitious notion
of hell and the devil.

00:25:35.800 --> 00:25:37.410 align:middle line:90%
So that was first and foremost.

00:25:37.410 --> 00:25:42.080 align:middle line:84%
But then, life is a classroom
as well as a playground.

00:25:42.080 --> 00:25:44.280 align:middle line:90%
And we're here with free will.

00:25:44.280 --> 00:25:46.780 align:middle line:84%
And what I wanted
to illustrate was

00:25:46.780 --> 00:25:53.560 align:middle line:84%
that those on the other
side with enough altitude,

00:25:53.560 --> 00:25:55.220 align:middle line:84%
so to speak, through
experience as

00:25:55.220 --> 00:25:58.020 align:middle line:84%
opposed to new souls who are
on the other side frantically

00:25:58.020 --> 00:26:02.190 align:middle line:84%
trying to create revenge, and
rush back into the jungles--

00:26:02.190 --> 00:26:05.250 align:middle line:84%
because no doubt
that would happen.

00:26:05.250 --> 00:26:08.660 align:middle line:84%
Those with the
wherewithal to see more

00:26:08.660 --> 00:26:11.730 align:middle line:84%
clearly realize-- and
they're shown undoubtedly.

00:26:11.730 --> 00:26:12.640 align:middle line:90%
Why wouldn't they be?

00:26:12.640 --> 00:26:13.812 align:middle line:90%
God adores us there.

00:26:13.812 --> 00:26:14.520 align:middle line:90%
There are angels.

00:26:14.520 --> 00:26:17.670 align:middle line:84%
There are intermediary
counselors and helpers.

00:26:17.670 --> 00:26:19.350 align:middle line:84%
Show them that they
could have handled

00:26:19.350 --> 00:26:24.090 align:middle line:84%
their funk, their dilemma,
their crises in a different way

00:26:24.090 --> 00:26:25.130 align:middle line:90%
other suicide.

00:26:25.130 --> 00:26:27.120 align:middle line:90%
And their rehabilitation begins.

00:26:27.120 --> 00:26:28.390 align:middle line:90%
But they are welcomed home.

00:26:28.390 --> 00:26:29.460 align:middle line:90%
They are loved.

00:26:29.460 --> 00:26:30.350 align:middle line:90%
They are adored.

00:26:30.350 --> 00:26:32.080 align:middle line:90%
We all are.

00:26:32.080 --> 00:26:33.530 align:middle line:90%
And so that was the point there.

00:26:33.530 --> 00:26:36.690 align:middle line:84%
And I go to great lengths
throughout the book to say,

00:26:36.690 --> 00:26:39.150 align:middle line:84%
yeah, there's no devil,
or hell, and it is super

00:26:39.150 --> 00:26:40.830 align:middle line:90%
awesome on the other side.

00:26:40.830 --> 00:26:43.290 align:middle line:84%
But there's also
a line of people

00:26:43.290 --> 00:26:45.150 align:middle line:84%
waiting to get back
into these most

00:26:45.150 --> 00:26:48.350 align:middle line:84%
awesome, glorious, magnificent
jungles of time and space.

00:26:48.350 --> 00:26:50.520 align:middle line:84%
And so my book is
no excuse for anyone

00:26:50.520 --> 00:26:52.730 align:middle line:90%
to end their life prematurely.

00:26:52.730 --> 00:26:55.780 align:middle line:84%
And I go to great lengths
to cover that face as well.

00:26:55.780 --> 00:26:58.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And in the letter,
he apologized to his mom

00:26:58.270 --> 00:27:04.780 align:middle line:84%
for taking his life, and
forgave her for the life

00:27:04.780 --> 00:27:07.140 align:middle line:90%
that she created for him.

00:27:07.140 --> 00:27:09.680 align:middle line:84%
If that were to be
real, I mean, that

00:27:09.680 --> 00:27:12.610 align:middle line:84%
was such a deep perspective
to look from, Mike.

00:27:12.610 --> 00:27:15.120 align:middle line:84%
You have this
unbelievable ability

00:27:15.120 --> 00:27:18.750 align:middle line:84%
to look from an outer
perspective that

00:27:18.750 --> 00:27:19.640 align:middle line:90%
isn't in this world.

00:27:19.640 --> 00:27:21.580 align:middle line:90%
It's really beautiful.

00:27:21.580 --> 00:27:23.850 align:middle line:84%
Let's take a look here at
Mike talking about the book.

