00:47:26.140 --> 00:47:28.640 align:middle line:84%
to where I was thinking
about, Orlando.

00:47:28.640 --> 00:47:31.660 align:middle line:84%
Now, a lot of people in life
have end results that are,

00:47:31.660 --> 00:47:34.640 align:middle line:84%
as we just said, life is
hard, people are mean,

00:47:34.640 --> 00:47:37.760 align:middle line:84%
it's all a test,
God decides-- all

00:47:37.760 --> 00:47:41.220 align:middle line:84%
of these things that
aren't true as reality,

00:47:41.220 --> 00:47:43.320 align:middle line:84%
as features of reality,
but they become

00:47:43.320 --> 00:47:45.340 align:middle line:84%
true for the person
claiming them.

00:47:45.340 --> 00:47:47.550 align:middle line:84%
So life is hard,
people are mean,

00:47:47.550 --> 00:47:51.470 align:middle line:84%
as you go through
your business, you're

00:47:51.470 --> 00:47:53.680 align:middle line:84%
going to find that
life is very hard,

00:47:53.680 --> 00:47:57.430 align:middle line:84%
and you're going to draw
into your realm mean people.

00:47:57.430 --> 00:48:02.140 align:middle line:84%
Or you might think life is
great, the universe loves me,

00:48:02.140 --> 00:48:06.320 align:middle line:84%
but I'm not good with math, and
money has always been elusive.

00:48:06.320 --> 00:48:09.320 align:middle line:84%
Now you've got
contradictory end results,

00:48:09.320 --> 00:48:13.180 align:middle line:84%
and so you're setting yourself
up for a kind of a quagmire,

00:48:13.180 --> 00:48:15.260 align:middle line:84%
where there will
be the unexpected.

00:48:15.260 --> 00:48:17.700 align:middle line:84%
But as we said about
paint a moment ago,

00:48:17.700 --> 00:48:19.430 align:middle line:90%
this is a great red flag.

00:48:19.430 --> 00:48:21.550 align:middle line:84%
This is like, hey, there's
a chink in your armor

00:48:21.550 --> 00:48:23.160 align:middle line:84%
that you didn't
even know you had.

00:48:23.160 --> 00:48:27.140 align:middle line:84%
But now there's been this slip,
this accident, this whatever,

00:48:27.140 --> 00:48:31.890 align:middle line:84%
that's telling you you can and
should ask for more clarity.

00:48:31.890 --> 00:48:34.410 align:middle line:84%
You should reexamine
your thoughts.

00:48:34.410 --> 00:48:36.240 align:middle line:84%
Pay more attention
to your words,

00:48:36.240 --> 00:48:38.880 align:middle line:90%
and get to a place of clarity.

00:48:38.880 --> 00:48:42.300 align:middle line:84%
And I would like to add also to
that, because a lot of people

00:48:42.300 --> 00:48:45.410 align:middle line:84%
will ask in my live
audiences, what

00:48:45.410 --> 00:48:47.390 align:middle line:84%
do you do when
everything's going well,

00:48:47.390 --> 00:48:49.970 align:middle line:84%
and you're feeling great
about life, and then wham,

00:48:49.970 --> 00:48:53.700 align:middle line:90%
you're blindsided by bad stuff?

00:48:53.700 --> 00:48:57.530 align:middle line:84%
And with a proper understanding
of the nature of reality,

00:48:57.530 --> 00:48:59.490 align:middle line:84%
including our choices
that brought us here,

00:48:59.490 --> 00:49:02.030 align:middle line:84%
including that we all
survive, we all rock and roll,

00:49:02.030 --> 00:49:04.410 align:middle line:84%
everyone beats cancer,
maybe not this lifetime,

00:49:04.410 --> 00:49:08.820 align:middle line:84%
but beyond in that light,
then all of a sudden,

00:49:08.820 --> 00:49:11.760 align:middle line:84%
from those perhaps
heightened perspectives,

00:49:11.760 --> 00:49:14.220 align:middle line:84%
you realize there
is no bad stuff.

00:49:14.220 --> 00:49:18.220 align:middle line:84%
There is no junk, gunk, or crap
that lands in anyone's life.

00:49:18.220 --> 00:49:21.800 align:middle line:84%
It's all like a stepping stone
to higher, greater, better

00:49:21.800 --> 00:49:23.950 align:middle line:90%
than you even knew existed.

00:49:23.950 --> 00:49:27.930 align:middle line:84%
That was otherwise unreachable
to you with your prior mindset.

00:49:27.930 --> 00:49:31.010 align:middle line:84%
So you know whether it's
cancer, or a car accident,

00:49:31.010 --> 00:49:35.320 align:middle line:84%
or a divorce, or whatever,
these are invitations

00:49:35.320 --> 00:49:38.860 align:middle line:84%
for you to go to a higher
orbit than you even knew

00:49:38.860 --> 00:49:40.220 align:middle line:90%
existed before.

00:49:40.220 --> 00:49:42.550 align:middle line:84%
And so long as you're not
kicking, and screaming,

00:49:42.550 --> 00:49:45.800 align:middle line:84%
and cursing, and resisting the
whole way, which just sets up

00:49:45.800 --> 00:49:48.820 align:middle line:84%
a war, you're just resisting
the entire universe,

00:49:48.820 --> 00:49:50.120 align:middle line:90%
which is futile--

00:49:50.120 --> 00:49:52.365 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Which is a lot of work.

00:49:52.365 --> 00:49:53.550 align:middle line:90%
>>DOOLEY: It's awful.

00:49:53.550 --> 00:49:56.970 align:middle line:84%
Then, you can open yourself
up to higher thinking,

00:49:56.970 --> 00:49:58.070 align:middle line:90%
to greater truths.

00:49:58.070 --> 00:49:59.950 align:middle line:84%
Which doesn't mean
capitulate to cancer,

00:49:59.950 --> 00:50:02.860 align:middle line:84%
or just say make
the best of the fact

00:50:02.860 --> 00:50:04.760 align:middle line:84%
that your maimed from
the car accident.

00:50:04.760 --> 00:50:07.800 align:middle line:84%
It's like, no, you're
not going to accept that.

00:50:07.800 --> 00:50:11.990 align:middle line:84%
But you will accept
what happened,

00:50:11.990 --> 00:50:14.410 align:middle line:84%
so that you can therefore
plant new seeds,

00:50:14.410 --> 00:50:18.740 align:middle line:84%
have a heightened perspective,
and live grander than ever

00:50:18.740 --> 00:50:19.817 align:middle line:90%
before.

00:50:19.817 --> 00:50:20.900 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So do you do that?

00:50:20.900 --> 00:50:24.220 align:middle line:84%
Do you set up what your next
step is through your words?

00:50:24.220 --> 00:50:26.010 align:middle line:90%
Do you practice all of this?

00:50:26.010 --> 00:50:31.010 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: I do the only
seemingly on the face

00:50:31.010 --> 00:50:34.340 align:middle line:84%
spiritual thing I do is every
morning before I go to work,

00:50:34.340 --> 00:50:38.470 align:middle line:84%
I visualize with the timer
in my office, my home office,

00:50:38.470 --> 00:50:40.680 align:middle line:90%
for about 4 and 1/2 minutes.

00:50:40.680 --> 00:50:41.660 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

00:50:41.660 --> 00:50:47.660 align:middle line:84%
The only deviation
from normal life.

00:50:47.660 --> 00:50:51.090 align:middle line:84%
Normal life, I would argue,
is very spiritual for me.

00:50:51.090 --> 00:50:53.220 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I do see
the good in people.

00:50:53.220 --> 00:50:54.860 align:middle line:90%
I do look for God in their eyes.

00:50:54.860 --> 00:50:57.840 align:middle line:90%
I do try to take the high road.

00:50:57.840 --> 00:50:59.970 align:middle line:90%
I'm kind, benevolent.

00:50:59.970 --> 00:51:02.660 align:middle line:84%
I'd like to think I am
in all those regards.

00:51:02.660 --> 00:51:06.050 align:middle line:84%
And I'm always aiming
for greater, bigger,

00:51:06.050 --> 00:51:08.880 align:middle line:84%
in my own personal,
private, rocking life,

00:51:08.880 --> 00:51:11.380 align:middle line:84%
and in reaching more
people with messages

00:51:11.380 --> 00:51:15.030 align:middle line:84%
that it resonate with
greater and greater numbers.

00:51:15.030 --> 00:51:17.320 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So where do
you go from here?

00:51:17.320 --> 00:51:21.700 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: I tell my audiences
in my crises 15 years ago,

00:51:21.700 --> 00:51:24.700 align:middle line:84%
I came up with four general end
results, wealth and abundance,

00:51:24.700 --> 00:51:26.930 align:middle line:84%
creative fulfilling work,
friends and laughter,

00:51:26.930 --> 00:51:28.490 align:middle line:90%
international travel.

00:51:28.490 --> 00:51:31.220 align:middle line:84%
And those will be my
guiding lights forever more.

00:51:31.220 --> 00:51:35.717 align:middle line:84%
I don't need anything
more specific than that.

00:51:35.717 --> 00:51:37.050 align:middle line:90%
Like, I'm going to write a book.

00:51:37.050 --> 00:51:38.550 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to do this.

00:51:38.550 --> 00:51:40.390 align:middle line:84%
Then you're messing
with the cursed house.

00:51:40.390 --> 00:51:42.160 align:middle line:84%
You're carrying the weight of
the world on your shoulders.

00:51:42.160 --> 00:51:43.410 align:middle line:90%
Now, I will write more books.

00:51:43.410 --> 00:51:44.740 align:middle line:90%
I will give more talks.

00:51:44.740 --> 00:51:47.760 align:middle line:84%
And I will knock on
more doors forever more.

00:51:47.760 --> 00:51:51.070 align:middle line:84%
But there may be a vehicle
of expression or a way

00:51:51.070 --> 00:51:53.923 align:middle line:84%
for me teach that's not
even on the radar right now.

00:51:53.923 --> 00:51:54.422 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:51:54.422 --> 00:51:55.610 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:51:55.610 --> 00:51:59.200 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: And I would slam shut
the door on such possibilities

00:51:59.200 --> 00:52:02.090 align:middle line:84%
if I insisted on, I'm going
to write, I'm going to speak.

00:52:02.090 --> 00:52:04.660 align:middle line:84%
So I'm going to
knock on all doors,

00:52:04.660 --> 00:52:08.970 align:middle line:84%
and see what happens, while
commanding the universe

00:52:08.970 --> 00:52:11.430 align:middle line:84%
with my overall big
picture end results

00:52:11.430 --> 00:52:14.550 align:middle line:84%
of a rocking, happy,
joyful life, which

00:52:14.550 --> 00:52:16.470 align:middle line:84%
leaves room for
great relationships,

00:52:16.470 --> 00:52:18.910 align:middle line:90%
and my new young family.

00:52:18.910 --> 00:52:20.220 align:middle line:90%
Infinite possibilities.

00:52:20.220 --> 00:52:21.902 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You have a baby.

00:52:21.902 --> 00:52:24.110 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: I have a one year,
one-month-old baby girl.

00:52:24.110 --> 00:52:25.665 align:middle line:90%
I'm a first time dad.

00:52:25.665 --> 00:52:26.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Awesome.

00:52:26.430 --> 00:52:29.410 align:middle line:84%
It's so exciting, because
all that you've taught,

00:52:29.410 --> 00:52:32.120 align:middle line:84%
and all that you teach,
you get to now impart

00:52:32.120 --> 00:52:33.700 align:middle line:90%
upon this little one.

00:52:33.700 --> 00:52:36.492 align:middle line:84%
However, the mundane
does still occur.

00:52:36.492 --> 00:52:37.450 align:middle line:90%
You still have diapers.

00:52:37.450 --> 00:52:39.389 align:middle line:90%
And you still-- [LAUGHING]

00:52:39.389 --> 00:52:41.180 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: And that's
not so mundane, is it?

00:52:41.180 --> 00:52:45.410 align:middle line:84%
No, I think every moment,
it's all a miracle.

00:52:45.410 --> 00:52:47.260 align:middle line:90%
We don't have to do stuff.

00:52:47.260 --> 00:52:48.110 align:middle line:90%
We get to do.

00:52:48.110 --> 00:52:50.490 align:middle line:84%
That I get to change
one more pair of diapers

00:52:50.490 --> 00:52:53.055 align:middle line:90%
is like, what a crazy gift.

00:52:53.055 --> 00:52:55.680 align:middle line:84%
I didn't even know
to ask for the joy

00:52:55.680 --> 00:52:56.970 align:middle line:90%
that this girl has given me.

00:52:56.970 --> 00:52:57.610 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Aw.

00:52:57.610 --> 00:53:01.099 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: And it's part
of my amazing life.

00:53:01.099 --> 00:53:02.265 align:middle line:90%
And I want her to diversify.

00:53:02.265 --> 00:53:03.930 align:middle line:90%
I want her to enjoy life.

00:53:03.930 --> 00:53:07.695 align:middle line:84%
I want her to smell the
roses and see the miraculous

00:53:07.695 --> 00:53:08.780 align:middle line:90%
in the mundane.

00:53:08.780 --> 00:53:09.887 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:53:09.887 --> 00:53:11.720 align:middle line:84%
Now, I love what you
said here, because what

00:53:11.720 --> 00:53:16.240 align:middle line:84%
I got from this was, you don't
need to set big, huge goals.

00:53:16.240 --> 00:53:20.320 align:middle line:84%
You don't need to go after that
next million dollar pay raise.

00:53:20.320 --> 00:53:24.550 align:middle line:84%
You are happy with creating the
life that you have every day.

00:53:24.550 --> 00:53:27.010 align:middle line:84%
You're in that great
space of creating

00:53:27.010 --> 00:53:28.780 align:middle line:90%
every day what you love to do.

00:53:28.780 --> 00:53:32.490 align:middle line:84%
They're not these super peaks
in your life I'm seeing.

00:53:32.490 --> 00:53:36.530 align:middle line:84%
You're doing the slow
rise of greatness.

00:53:36.530 --> 00:53:37.450 align:middle line:90%
Do you feel that way?

00:53:37.450 --> 00:53:38.980 align:middle line:84%
You don't have these
super high dramas?

00:53:38.980 --> 00:53:39.605 align:middle line:90%
>>DOOLEY: Yeah.

00:53:39.605 --> 00:53:41.860 align:middle line:84%
Totally My number one lesson
in my full day workshop,

00:53:41.860 --> 00:53:45.640 align:middle line:84%
my trademark material, is
the ultimate end result

00:53:45.640 --> 00:53:47.660 align:middle line:90%
is always happiness.

00:53:47.660 --> 00:53:50.557 align:middle line:84%
And while that may
lack some luster--

00:53:50.557 --> 00:53:51.640 align:middle line:90%
I mean, what is happiness?

00:53:51.640 --> 00:53:53.220 align:middle line:84%
Everyone has to define
it for themselves.

00:53:53.220 --> 00:53:55.390 align:middle line:84%
That's why I say, go ahead
and have some priorities.

00:53:55.390 --> 00:53:58.260 align:middle line:84%
Like, for me, they were those
four objectives-- abundance,

00:53:58.260 --> 00:54:01.420 align:middle line:90%
travel, friends, and laughter.

00:54:01.420 --> 00:54:03.090 align:middle line:90%
So those are my priorities.

00:54:03.090 --> 00:54:06.110 align:middle line:84%
But there's no, this book,
that contract, that deal,

00:54:06.110 --> 00:54:07.200 align:middle line:90%
this person.

00:54:07.200 --> 00:54:09.680 align:middle line:84%
Then, you carry the weight of
the world on your shoulders.

00:54:09.680 --> 00:54:12.700 align:middle line:84%
So I have gigantic
dreams of happiness

00:54:12.700 --> 00:54:16.590 align:middle line:84%
that I color in with
details, but those details I

00:54:16.590 --> 00:54:18.160 align:middle line:90%
don't attach to.

00:54:18.160 --> 00:54:21.030 align:middle line:84%
That leaves room for
infinite possibilities.

00:54:21.030 --> 00:54:23.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And that's where the
insights come for the Notes

00:54:23.860 --> 00:54:24.640 align:middle line:90%
From the Universe.

00:54:24.640 --> 00:54:27.840 align:middle line:84%
Because you're writing
life in a wave,

00:54:27.840 --> 00:54:30.281 align:middle line:84%
but I don't see these super
high peaks and valleys.

00:54:30.281 --> 00:54:32.780 align:middle line:84%
Because if you set yourself up
for that, and you don't get--

00:54:32.780 --> 00:54:33.530 align:middle line:90%
>>DOOLEY: That hurts.

00:54:33.530 --> 00:54:34.113 align:middle line:90%
And then what?

00:54:34.113 --> 00:54:37.720 align:middle line:90%
And then, you have to up it?

00:54:37.720 --> 00:54:40.680 align:middle line:84%
As you go down these paths that
we're talking about, knocking

00:54:40.680 --> 00:54:42.260 align:middle line:84%
on doors, even if
at first, it's kind

00:54:42.260 --> 00:54:44.700 align:middle line:84%
of a sucky path
to a job you hate,

00:54:44.700 --> 00:54:46.760 align:middle line:84%
when you understand the
truth about reality,

00:54:46.760 --> 00:54:48.840 align:middle line:84%
you become a lightning
rod for serendipity.

00:54:48.840 --> 00:54:50.840 align:middle line:84%
All of a sudden, you're
on the yellow brick road

00:54:50.840 --> 00:54:52.340 align:middle line:90%
a couple of years later.

00:54:52.340 --> 00:54:54.594 align:middle line:84%
All of a sudden,
happiness is your gig.

00:54:54.594 --> 00:54:57.010 align:middle line:84%
And you're coloring it here,
and you're coloring it there.

00:54:57.010 --> 00:54:58.510 align:middle line:84%
And you're tweaking
the machinery.

00:54:58.510 --> 00:55:01.760 align:middle line:84%
And you've built a foundation,
which is all important.

00:55:01.760 --> 00:55:04.070 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, your
success is precarious.

00:55:04.070 --> 00:55:06.070 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, you feel like
it could be taken away.

00:55:06.070 --> 00:55:08.530 align:middle line:84%
All of a sudden,
you feel vulnerable.

00:55:08.530 --> 00:55:12.240 align:middle line:84%
But this steadier
approach, with happiness

00:55:12.240 --> 00:55:17.157 align:middle line:84%
as your light, priorities in
other areas, is the formula,

00:55:17.157 --> 00:55:17.740 align:middle line:90%
is the ticket.

00:55:17.740 --> 00:55:18.950 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Even though
you have things

00:55:18.950 --> 00:55:20.658 align:middle line:84%
like kids going off
to college, or having

00:55:20.658 --> 00:55:23.300 align:middle line:84%
to start a new job, or this one
implodes, and that one starts,

00:55:23.300 --> 00:55:25.007 align:middle line:84%
you just ride it
like it's the wave.

00:55:25.007 --> 00:55:26.590 align:middle line:84%
Setting your intentions
along the way,

00:55:26.590 --> 00:55:29.090 align:middle line:84%
making sure that your
language is in coherence

00:55:29.090 --> 00:55:31.300 align:middle line:84%
with who you're being
around it, and you just

00:55:31.300 --> 00:55:32.379 align:middle line:90%
create life that way.

00:55:32.379 --> 00:55:33.920 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: As a Note
From the Universe

00:55:33.920 --> 00:55:36.680 align:middle line:84%
once said, whether it's for
other people or yourself,

00:55:36.680 --> 00:55:38.240 align:middle line:90%
always wish for the best.

00:55:38.240 --> 00:55:39.780 align:middle line:90%
You can leave it that.

00:55:39.780 --> 00:55:42.340 align:middle line:84%
And then whatever
happens, know that it was.

00:55:42.340 --> 00:55:44.660 align:middle line:84%
And then, you don't
start labeling things.

00:55:44.660 --> 00:55:45.590 align:middle line:90%
That was bad.

00:55:45.590 --> 00:55:46.860 align:middle line:90%
I must be flawed.

00:55:46.860 --> 00:55:48.950 align:middle line:84%
I have an invisible,
limiting self-sabotage.

00:55:48.950 --> 00:55:50.180 align:middle line:90%
It's all good.

00:55:50.180 --> 00:55:52.720 align:middle line:84%
It's all playing to
your greater good.

00:55:52.720 --> 00:55:54.010 align:middle line:90%
See it as good.

00:55:54.010 --> 00:55:55.030 align:middle line:90%
Look for the gift.

00:55:55.030 --> 00:55:57.780 align:middle line:84%
And even if you don't know what
the gift was, it was imparted.

00:55:57.780 --> 00:55:59.550 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to
figure out how you

00:55:59.550 --> 00:56:02.240 align:middle line:84%
got where you are,
particularly if it's painful,

00:56:02.240 --> 00:56:04.260 align:middle line:84%
to otherwise figure out
how to move from it.

00:56:04.260 --> 00:56:06.236 align:middle line:90%
And that's kind of my lesson.

00:56:06.236 --> 00:56:07.170 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Beautiful.

00:56:07.170 --> 00:56:09.307 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much for
giving us your wisdom.

00:56:09.307 --> 00:56:10.390 align:middle line:90%
>>DOOLEY: Thank you, Lisa.

00:56:10.390 --> 00:56:11.910 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And for hanging
out with me for the hour.

00:56:11.910 --> 00:56:12.761 align:middle line:90%
It's been wonderful.

00:56:12.761 --> 00:56:14.260 align:middle line:84%
>>DOOLEY: I've
enjoyed every minute.

00:56:14.260 --> 00:56:15.362 align:middle line:90%
Thank you so much.

